{
  "texts": [
    "During the inference, a simple 𝐾-Means algorithm is utilized to select appropriate common and personalized prompts to guide the pre-trained model to encode new image tokens for classification.",
    "Common PromptsAs shown in Figure 2, we design a continually tuned common prompting strategy for guiding the learning model to extract shared knowledge across each domain.",
    "The common prompts are tinysized parameters that are tuned by loss gradient calculated by prediction on each domain data sample.",
    "At this moment, the entire parameters of the pre-trained model are frozen so that the generation variation of the model would only be affected by inputs and prompts.For the sake of simplification, here we describe the prompting on the image encoder side.",
    "Formally, for the 𝑖-th domain dataset D 𝑠 = {𝑥 𝑠,𝑖, 𝑦 𝑠,𝑖 } 𝑁 𝑖=1, the image tokens 𝒙 𝑠,𝑖 𝑒𝑚𝑏 ∈ R 𝐸 𝐼 ×𝐷 are obtained by the initial convolutional neural network embedding layer."
  ]
}